36TPrecision GetHigherPrecision(TPrecision left, TPrecision right)
37{
38 return left > right ? left : right;
39}

41TConstantUnion *Vectorize(const TConstantUnion &constant, size_t size)
42{
43 TConstantUnion *constUnion = new TConstantUnion[size];
44 for (size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i)
45 constUnion[i] = constant;
46
47 return constUnion;
48}
49
50void UndefinedConstantFoldingError(const TSourceLoc &loc,
51 TOperator op,
52 TBasicType basicType,
53 TDiagnostics *diagnostics,
54 TConstantUnion *result)
55{
56 diagnostics->warning(loc, "operation result is undefined for the values passed in",
57 GetOperatorString(op));
58
59 switch (basicType)
60 {
61 case EbtFloat:
62 result->setFConst(0.0f);
63 break;
64 case EbtInt:
65 result->setIConst(0);
66 break;
67 case EbtUInt:
68 result->setUConst(0u);
69 break;
70 case EbtBool:
71 result->setBConst(false);
72 break;
73 default:
74 break;
75 }
76}
77
78float VectorLength(const TConstantUnion *paramArray, size_t paramArraySize)
79{
80 float result = 0.0f;
81 for (size_t i = 0; i < paramArraySize; i++)
82 {
83 float f = paramArray[i].getFConst();
84 result += f * f;
85 }
86 return sqrtf(result);
87}
88
89float VectorDotProduct(const TConstantUnion *paramArray1,
90 const TConstantUnion *paramArray2,
91 size_t paramArraySize)
92{
93 float result = 0.0f;
94 for (size_t i = 0; i < paramArraySize; i++)
95 result += paramArray1[i].getFConst() * paramArray2[i].getFConst();
96 return result;
97}

99TIntermTyped *CreateFoldedNode(const TConstantUnion *constArray, const TIntermTyped *originalNode)
100{
101 ASSERT(constArray != nullptr);
102 // Note that we inherit whatever qualifier the folded node had. Nodes may be constant folded
103 // without being qualified as constant.
104 TIntermTyped *folded = new TIntermConstantUnion(constArray, originalNode->getType());
105 folded->setLine(originalNode->getLine());
106 return folded;
107}
108
109angle::Matrix<float> GetMatrix(const TConstantUnion *paramArray,
110 const unsigned int rows,
111 const unsigned int cols)
112{
113 std::vector<float> elements;
114 for (size_t i = 0; i < rows * cols; i++)
115 elements.push_back(paramArray[i].getFConst());
116 // Transpose is used since the Matrix constructor expects arguments in row-major order,
117 // whereas the paramArray is in column-major order. Rows/cols parameters are also flipped below
118 // so that the created matrix will have the expected dimensions after the transpose.
119 return angle::Matrix<float>(elements, cols, rows).transpose();
120}
121
122angle::Matrix<float> GetMatrix(const TConstantUnion *paramArray, const unsigned int size)
123{
124 std::vector<float> elements;
125 for (size_t i = 0; i < size * size; i++)
126 elements.push_back(paramArray[i].getFConst());
127 // Transpose is used since the Matrix constructor expects arguments in row-major order,
128 // whereas the paramArray is in column-major order.
129 return angle::Matrix<float>(elements, size).transpose();
130}
131
132void SetUnionArrayFromMatrix(const angle::Matrix<float> &m, TConstantUnion *resultArray)
133{
134 // Transpose is used since the input Matrix is in row-major order,
135 // whereas the actual result should be in column-major order.
136 angle::Matrix<float> result = m.transpose();
137 std::vector<float> resultElements = result.elements();
138 for (size_t i = 0; i < resultElements.size(); i++)
139 resultArray[i].setFConst(resultElements[i]);
140}

142bool CanFoldAggregateBuiltInOp(TOperator op)
143{
144 switch (op)
145 {
146 case EOpAtan:
147 case EOpPow:
148 case EOpMod:
149 case EOpMin:
150 case EOpMax:
151 case EOpClamp:
152 case EOpMix:
153 case EOpStep:
154 case EOpSmoothstep:
155 case EOpFma:
156 case EOpLdexp:
157 case EOpMulMatrixComponentWise:
158 case EOpOuterProduct:
159 case EOpEqualComponentWise:
160 case EOpNotEqualComponentWise:
161 case EOpLessThanComponentWise:
162 case EOpLessThanEqualComponentWise:
163 case EOpGreaterThanComponentWise:
164 case EOpGreaterThanEqualComponentWise:
165 case EOpDistance:
166 case EOpDot:
167 case EOpCross:
168 case EOpFaceforward:
169 case EOpReflect:
170 case EOpRefract:
171 case EOpBitfieldExtract:
172 case EOpBitfieldInsert:
173 return true;
174 default:
175 return false;
176 }
177}

197#define REPLACE_IF_IS(node, type, original, replacement) \
198 do \
199 { \
200 if (node == original) \
201 { \
202 node = static_cast<type *>(replacement); \
203 return true; \
204 } \
205 } while (0)

229size_t TIntermLoop::getChildCount() const
230{
231 return (mInit ? 1 : 0) + (mCond ? 1 : 0) + (mExpr ? 1 : 0) + (mBody ? 1 : 0);
232}
233
234TIntermNode *TIntermLoop::getChildNode(size_t index) const
235{
236 TIntermNode *children[4];
237 unsigned int childIndex = 0;
238 if (mInit)
239 {
240 children[childIndex] = mInit;
241 ++childIndex;
242 }
243 if (mCond)
244 {
245 children[childIndex] = mCond;
246 ++childIndex;
247 }
248 if (mExpr)
249 {
250 children[childIndex] = mExpr;
251 ++childIndex;
252 }
253 if (mBody)
254 {
255 children[childIndex] = mBody;
256 ++childIndex;
257 }
258 ASSERT(index < childIndex);
259 return children[index];
260}
261
262bool TIntermLoop::replaceChildNode(TIntermNode *original, TIntermNode *replacement)
263{
264 ASSERT(original != nullptr); // This risks replacing multiple children.
265 REPLACE_IF_IS(mInit, TIntermNode, original, replacement);
266 REPLACE_IF_IS(mCond, TIntermTyped, original, replacement);
267 REPLACE_IF_IS(mExpr, TIntermTyped, original, replacement);
268 REPLACE_IF_IS(mBody, TIntermBlock, original, replacement);
269 return false;
270}

503bool TIntermAggregateBase::replaceChildNodeInternal(TIntermNode *original, TIntermNode *replacement)
504{
505 auto &seq = *getSequence();
506 for (auto *&node : seq)
507 {
508 REPLACE_IF_IS(node, TIntermNode, original, replacement);
509 }
510 return false;
511}
512
513bool TIntermAggregateBase::replaceChildNodeWithMultiple(TIntermNode *original,
514 const TIntermSequence &replacements)
515{
516 auto &seq = *getSequence();
517 for (auto it = seq.begin(); it < seq.end(); ++it)
518 {
519 if (*it == original)
520 {
521 it = seq.erase(it);
522 seq.insert(it, replacements.begin(), replacements.end());
523 return true;
524 }
525 }
526 return false;
527}
528
529bool TIntermAggregateBase::insertChildNodes(TIntermSequence::size_type position,
530 const TIntermSequence &insertions)
531{
532 auto &seq = *getSequence();
533 if (position > seq.size())
534 {
535 return false;
536 }
537 auto it = seq.begin() + position;
538 seq.insert(it, insertions.begin(), insertions.end());
539 return true;
540}

594TIntermAggregate::TIntermAggregate(const TFunction *func,
595 const TType &type,
596 TOperator op,
597 TIntermSequence *arguments)
598 : TIntermOperator(op, type),
599 mUseEmulatedFunction(false),
600 mGotPrecisionFromChildren(false),
601 mFunction(func)
602{
603 if (arguments != nullptr)
604 {
605 mArguments.swap(*arguments);
606 }
607 ASSERT(mFunction == nullptr || mFunction->symbolType() != SymbolType::Empty);
608 setPrecisionAndQualifier();
609}
610
611void TIntermAggregate::setPrecisionAndQualifier()
612{
613 mType.setQualifier(EvqTemporary);
614 if (mOp == EOpCallBuiltInFunction)
615 {
616 setBuiltInFunctionPrecision();
617 }
618 else if (!isFunctionCall())
619 {
620 if (isConstructor())
621 {
622 // Structs should not be precision qualified, the individual members may be.
623 // Built-in types on the other hand should be precision qualified.
624 if (getBasicType() != EbtStruct)
625 {
626 setPrecisionFromChildren();
627 }
628 }
629 else
630 {
631 setPrecisionForBuiltInOp();
632 }
633 if (areChildrenConstQualified())
634 {
635 mType.setQualifier(EvqConst);
636 }
637 }
638}
639
640bool TIntermAggregate::areChildrenConstQualified()
641{
642 for (TIntermNode *&arg : mArguments)
643 {
644 TIntermTyped *typedArg = arg->getAsTyped();
645 if (typedArg && typedArg->getQualifier() != EvqConst)
646 {
647 return false;
648 }
649 }
650 return true;
651}
652
653void TIntermAggregate::setPrecisionFromChildren()
654{
655 mGotPrecisionFromChildren = true;
656 if (getBasicType() == EbtBool)
657 {
658 mType.setPrecision(EbpUndefined);
659 return;
660 }
661
662 TPrecision precision = EbpUndefined;
663 TIntermSequence::iterator childIter = mArguments.begin();
664 while (childIter != mArguments.end())
665 {
666 TIntermTyped *typed = (*childIter)->getAsTyped();
667 if (typed)
668 precision = GetHigherPrecision(typed->getPrecision(), precision);
669 ++childIter;
670 }
671 mType.setPrecision(precision);
672}
673
674void TIntermAggregate::setPrecisionForBuiltInOp()
675{
676 ASSERT(!isConstructor());
677 ASSERT(!isFunctionCall());
678 if (!setPrecisionForSpecialBuiltInOp())
679 {
680 setPrecisionFromChildren();
681 }
682}
683
684bool TIntermAggregate::setPrecisionForSpecialBuiltInOp()
685{
686 switch (mOp)
687 {
688 case EOpBitfieldExtract:
689 mType.setPrecision(mArguments[0]->getAsTyped()->getPrecision());
690 mGotPrecisionFromChildren = true;
691 return true;
692 case EOpBitfieldInsert:
693 mType.setPrecision(GetHigherPrecision(mArguments[0]->getAsTyped()->getPrecision(),
694 mArguments[1]->getAsTyped()->getPrecision()));
695 mGotPrecisionFromChildren = true;
696 return true;
697 case EOpUaddCarry:
698 case EOpUsubBorrow:
699 mType.setPrecision(EbpHigh);
700 return true;
701 default:
702 return false;
703 }
704}
705
706void TIntermAggregate::setBuiltInFunctionPrecision()
707{
708 // All built-ins returning bool should be handled as ops, not functions.
709 ASSERT(getBasicType() != EbtBool);
710 ASSERT(mOp == EOpCallBuiltInFunction);
711
712 TPrecision precision = EbpUndefined;
713 for (TIntermNode *arg : mArguments)
714 {
715 TIntermTyped *typed = arg->getAsTyped();
716 // ESSL spec section 8: texture functions get their precision from the sampler.
717 if (typed && IsSampler(typed->getBasicType()))
718 {
719 precision = typed->getPrecision();
720 break;
721 }
722 }
723 // ESSL 3.0 spec section 8: textureSize always gets highp precision.
724 // All other functions that take a sampler are assumed to be texture functions.
725 if (mFunction->name() == "textureSize")
726 mType.setPrecision(EbpHigh);
727 else
728 mType.setPrecision(precision);
729}

731const char *TIntermAggregate::functionName() const
732{
733 ASSERT(!isConstructor());
734 switch (mOp)
735 {
736 case EOpCallInternalRawFunction:
737 case EOpCallBuiltInFunction:
738 case EOpCallFunctionInAST:
739 return mFunction->name().data();
740 default:
741 return GetOperatorString(mOp);
742 }
743}
744
745bool TIntermAggregate::hasConstantValue() const
746{
747 if (!isConstructor())
748 {
749 return false;
750 }
751 for (TIntermNode *constructorArg : mArguments)
752 {
753 if (!constructorArg->getAsTyped()->hasConstantValue())
754 {
755 return false;
756 }
757 }
758 return true;
759}
760
761const TConstantUnion *TIntermAggregate::getConstantValue() const
762{
763 if (!hasConstantValue())
764 {
765 return nullptr;
766 }
767 ASSERT(isConstructor());
768 ASSERT(mArguments.size() > 0u);
769
770 TConstantUnion *constArray = nullptr;
771 if (isArray())
772 {
773 size_t elementSize = mArguments.front()->getAsTyped()->getType().getObjectSize();
774 constArray = new TConstantUnion[elementSize * getOutermostArraySize()];
775
776 size_t elementOffset = 0u;
777 for (TIntermNode *constructorArg : mArguments)
778 {
779 const TConstantUnion *elementConstArray =
780 constructorArg->getAsTyped()->getConstantValue();
781 ASSERT(elementConstArray);
782 size_t elementSizeBytes = sizeof(TConstantUnion) * elementSize;
783 memcpy(static_cast<void *>(&constArray[elementOffset]),
784 static_cast<const void *>(elementConstArray), elementSizeBytes);
785 elementOffset += elementSize;
786 }
787 return constArray;
788 }
789
790 size_t resultSize = getType().getObjectSize();
791 constArray = new TConstantUnion[resultSize];
792 TBasicType basicType = getBasicType();
793
794 size_t resultIndex = 0u;
795
796 if (mArguments.size() == 1u)
797 {
798 TIntermNode *argument = mArguments.front();
799 TIntermTyped *argumentTyped = argument->getAsTyped();
800 const TConstantUnion *argumentConstantValue = argumentTyped->getConstantValue();
801 // Check the special case of constructing a matrix diagonal from a single scalar,
802 // or a vector from a single scalar.
803 if (argumentTyped->getType().getObjectSize() == 1u)
804 {
805 if (isMatrix())
806 {
807 int resultCols = getType().getCols();
808 int resultRows = getType().getRows();
809 for (int col = 0; col < resultCols; ++col)
810 {
811 for (int row = 0; row < resultRows; ++row)
812 {
813 if (col == row)
814 {
815 constArray[resultIndex].cast(basicType, argumentConstantValue[0]);
816 }
817 else
818 {
819 constArray[resultIndex].setFConst(0.0f);
820 }
821 ++resultIndex;
822 }
823 }
824 }
825 else
826 {
827 while (resultIndex < resultSize)
828 {
829 constArray[resultIndex].cast(basicType, argumentConstantValue[0]);
830 ++resultIndex;
831 }
832 }
833 ASSERT(resultIndex == resultSize);
834 return constArray;
835 }
836 else if (isMatrix() && argumentTyped->isMatrix())
837 {
838 // The special case of constructing a matrix from a matrix.
839 int argumentCols = argumentTyped->getType().getCols();
840 int argumentRows = argumentTyped->getType().getRows();
841 int resultCols = getType().getCols();
842 int resultRows = getType().getRows();
843 for (int col = 0; col < resultCols; ++col)
844 {
845 for (int row = 0; row < resultRows; ++row)
846 {
847 if (col < argumentCols && row < argumentRows)
848 {
849 constArray[resultIndex].cast(
850 basicType, argumentConstantValue[col * argumentRows + row]);
851 }
852 else if (col == row)
853 {
854 constArray[resultIndex].setFConst(1.0f);
855 }
856 else
857 {
858 constArray[resultIndex].setFConst(0.0f);
859 }
860 ++resultIndex;
861 }
862 }
863 ASSERT(resultIndex == resultSize);
864 return constArray;
865 }
866 }
867
868 for (TIntermNode *argument : mArguments)
869 {
870 TIntermTyped *argumentTyped = argument->getAsTyped();
871 size_t argumentSize = argumentTyped->getType().getObjectSize();
872 const TConstantUnion *argumentConstantValue = argumentTyped->getConstantValue();
873 for (size_t i = 0u; i < argumentSize; ++i)
874 {
875 if (resultIndex >= resultSize)
876 break;
877 constArray[resultIndex].cast(basicType, argumentConstantValue[i]);
878 ++resultIndex;
879 }
880 }
881 ASSERT(resultIndex == resultSize);
882 return constArray;
883}
884
885bool TIntermAggregate::hasSideEffects() const
886{
887 if (getQualifier() == EvqConst)
888 {
889 return false;
890 }
891 bool calledFunctionHasNoSideEffects =
892 isFunctionCall() && mFunction != nullptr && mFunction->isKnownToNotHaveSideEffects();
893 if (calledFunctionHasNoSideEffects || isConstructor())
894 {
895 for (TIntermNode *arg : mArguments)
896 {
897 if (arg->getAsTyped()->hasSideEffects())
898 {
899 return true;
900 }
901 }
902 return false;
903 }
904 // Conservatively assume most aggregate operators have side-effects
905 return true;
906}

1137bool TIntermOperator::isMultiplication() const
1138{
1139 switch (mOp)
1140 {
1141 case EOpMul:
1142 case EOpMatrixTimesMatrix:
1143 case EOpMatrixTimesVector:

1159{

1161 {
1162 case EOpCallFunctionInAST:
1163 case EOpCallBuiltInFunction:
1164 case EOpCallInternalRawFunction:
1165 return true;
1166 default:
1167 return false;
1168 }

1170
1171TOperator TIntermBinary::GetMulOpBasedOnOperands(const TType &left, const TType &right)
1172{
1173 if (left.isMatrix())
1174 {
1175 if (right.isMatrix())
1176 {
1177 return EOpMatrixTimesMatrix;
1178 }
1179 else
1180 {
1181 if (right.isVector())
1182 {
1183 return EOpMatrixTimesVector;
1184 }
1185 else
1186 {
1187 return EOpMatrixTimesScalar;
1188 }
1189 }
1190 }
1191 else
1192 {
1193 if (right.isMatrix())
1194 {
1195 if (left.isVector())
1196 {
1197 return EOpVectorTimesMatrix;
1198 }
1199 else
1200 {
1201 return EOpMatrixTimesScalar;
1202 }
1203 }
1204 else
1205 {
1206 // Neither operand is a matrix.
1207 if (left.isVector() == right.isVector())
1208 {
1209 // Leave as component product.
1210 return EOpMul;
1211 }
1212 else
1213 {
1214 return EOpVectorTimesScalar;
1215 }
1216 }
1217 }
1218}
1219
1220TOperator TIntermBinary::GetMulAssignOpBasedOnOperands(const TType &left, const TType &right)
1221{
1222 if (left.isMatrix())
1223 {
1224 if (right.isMatrix())
1225 {
1226 return EOpMatrixTimesMatrixAssign;
1227 }
1228 else
1229 {
1230 // right should be scalar, but this may not be validated yet.
1231 return EOpMatrixTimesScalarAssign;
1232 }
1233 }
1234 else
1235 {
1236 if (right.isMatrix())
1237 {
1238 // Left should be a vector, but this may not be validated yet.
1239 return EOpVectorTimesMatrixAssign;
1240 }
1241 else
1242 {
1243 // Neither operand is a matrix.
1244 if (left.isVector() == right.isVector())
1245 {
1246 // Leave as component product.
1247 return EOpMulAssign;
1248 }
1249 else
1250 {
1251 // left should be vector and right should be scalar, but this may not be validated
1252 // yet.
1253 return EOpVectorTimesScalarAssign;
1254 }
1255 }
1256 }
1257}
1258
1259//
1260// Make sure the type of a unary operator is appropriate for its
1261// combination of operation and operand type.
1262//
1263void TIntermUnary::promote()
1264{
1265 if (mOp == EOpArrayLength)
1266 {
1267 // Special case: the qualifier of .length() doesn't depend on the operand qualifier.
1268 setType(TType(EbtInt, EbpUndefined, EvqConst));
1269 return;
1270 }
1271
1272 TQualifier resultQualifier = EvqTemporary;
1273 if (mOperand->getQualifier() == EvqConst)
1274 resultQualifier = EvqConst;
1275
1276 unsigned char operandPrimarySize =
1277 static_cast<unsigned char>(mOperand->getType().getNominalSize());
1278 switch (mOp)
1279 {
1280 case EOpFloatBitsToInt:
1281 setType(TType(EbtInt, EbpHigh, resultQualifier, operandPrimarySize));
1282 break;
1283 case EOpFloatBitsToUint:
1284 setType(TType(EbtUInt, EbpHigh, resultQualifier, operandPrimarySize));
1285 break;
1286 case EOpIntBitsToFloat:
1287 case EOpUintBitsToFloat:
1288 setType(TType(EbtFloat, EbpHigh, resultQualifier, operandPrimarySize));
1289 break;
1290 case EOpPackSnorm2x16:
1291 case EOpPackUnorm2x16:
1292 case EOpPackHalf2x16:
1293 case EOpPackUnorm4x8:
1294 case EOpPackSnorm4x8:
1295 setType(TType(EbtUInt, EbpHigh, resultQualifier));
1296 break;
1297 case EOpUnpackSnorm2x16:
1298 case EOpUnpackUnorm2x16:
1299 setType(TType(EbtFloat, EbpHigh, resultQualifier, 2));
1300 break;
1301 case EOpUnpackHalf2x16:
1302 setType(TType(EbtFloat, EbpMedium, resultQualifier, 2));
1303 break;
1304 case EOpUnpackUnorm4x8:
1305 case EOpUnpackSnorm4x8:
1306 setType(TType(EbtFloat, EbpMedium, resultQualifier, 4));
1307 break;
1308 case EOpAny:
1309 case EOpAll:
1310 setType(TType(EbtBool, EbpUndefined, resultQualifier));
1311 break;
1312 case EOpLength:
1313 case EOpDeterminant:
1314 setType(TType(EbtFloat, mOperand->getType().getPrecision(), resultQualifier));
1315 break;
1316 case EOpTranspose:
1317 setType(TType(EbtFloat, mOperand->getType().getPrecision(), resultQualifier,
1318 static_cast<unsigned char>(mOperand->getType().getRows()),
1319 static_cast<unsigned char>(mOperand->getType().getCols())));
1320 break;
1321 case EOpIsinf:
1322 case EOpIsnan:
1323 setType(TType(EbtBool, EbpUndefined, resultQualifier, operandPrimarySize));
1324 break;
1325 case EOpBitfieldReverse:
1326 setType(TType(mOperand->getBasicType(), EbpHigh, resultQualifier, operandPrimarySize));
1327 break;
1328 case EOpBitCount:
1329 setType(TType(EbtInt, EbpLow, resultQualifier, operandPrimarySize));
1330 break;
1331 case EOpFindLSB:
1332 setType(TType(EbtInt, EbpLow, resultQualifier, operandPrimarySize));
1333 break;
1334 case EOpFindMSB:
1335 setType(TType(EbtInt, EbpLow, resultQualifier, operandPrimarySize));
1336 break;
1337 default:
1338 setType(mOperand->getType());
1339 mType.setQualifier(resultQualifier);
1340 break;
1341 }
1342}

1498{

1501 resultQualifier = EvqConst;
1502

1507
1508bool TIntermSwizzle::hasDuplicateOffsets() const
1509{
1510 if (mHasFoldedDuplicateOffsets)
1511 {
1512 return true;
1513 }
1514 int offsetCount[4] = {0u, 0u, 0u, 0u};
1515 for (const auto offset : mSwizzleOffsets)
1516 {
1517 offsetCount[offset]++;
1518 if (offsetCount[offset] > 1)
1519 {
1520 return true;
1521 }
1522 }
1523 return false;
1524}

1529}

1531bool TIntermSwizzle::offsetsMatch(int offset) const
1532{
1533 return mSwizzleOffsets.size() == 1 && mSwizzleOffsets[0] == offset;
1534}
1535
1536void TIntermSwizzle::writeOffsetsAsXYZW(TInfoSinkBase *out) const
1537{
1538 for (const int offset : mSwizzleOffsets)
1539 {
1540 switch (offset)
1541 {
1542 case 0:
1543 *out << "x";
1544 break;
1545 case 1:
1546 *out << "y";
1547 break;
1548 case 2:
1549 *out << "z";
1550 break;
1551 case 3:
1552 *out << "w";
1553 break;
1554 default:
1555 UNREACHABLE();
1556 }
1557 }
1558}
1559
1560TQualifier TIntermBinary::GetCommaQualifier(int shaderVersion,
1561 const TIntermTyped *left,
1562 const TIntermTyped *right)
1563{
1564 // ESSL3.00 section 12.43: The result of a sequence operator is not a constant-expression.
1565 if (shaderVersion >= 300 || left->getQualifier() != EvqConst ||
1566 right->getQualifier() != EvqConst)
1567 {
1568 return EvqTemporary;
1569 }
1570 return EvqConst;
1571}
1572
1573// Establishes the type of the result of the binary operation.
1574void TIntermBinary::promote()
1575{
1576 ASSERT(!isMultiplication() ||
1577 mOp == GetMulOpBasedOnOperands(mLeft->getType(), mRight->getType()));
1578
1579 // Comma is handled as a special case. Note that the comma node qualifier depends on the shader
1580 // version and so is not being set here.
1581 if (mOp == EOpComma)
1582 {
1583 setType(mRight->getType());
1584 return;
1585 }
1586
1587 // Base assumption: just make the type the same as the left
1588 // operand. Then only deviations from this need be coded.
1589 setType(mLeft->getType());
1590
1591 TQualifier resultQualifier = EvqConst;
1592 // Binary operations results in temporary variables unless both
1593 // operands are const.
1594 if (mLeft->getQualifier() != EvqConst || mRight->getQualifier() != EvqConst)
1595 {
1596 resultQualifier = EvqTemporary;
1597 getTypePointer()->setQualifier(EvqTemporary);
1598 }
1599
1600 // Handle indexing ops.
1601 switch (mOp)
1602 {
1603 case EOpIndexDirect:
1604 case EOpIndexIndirect:
1605 if (mLeft->isArray())
1606 {
1607 mType.toArrayElementType();
1608 }
1609 else if (mLeft->isMatrix())
1610 {
1611 setType(TType(mLeft->getBasicType(), mLeft->getPrecision(), resultQualifier,
1612 static_cast<unsigned char>(mLeft->getRows())));
1613 }
1614 else if (mLeft->isVector())
1615 {
1616 setType(TType(mLeft->getBasicType(), mLeft->getPrecision(), resultQualifier));
1617 }
1618 else
1619 {
1620 UNREACHABLE();
1621 }
1622 return;
1623 case EOpIndexDirectStruct:
1624 {
1625 const TFieldList &fields = mLeft->getType().getStruct()->fields();
1626 const int i = mRight->getAsConstantUnion()->getIConst(0);
1627 setType(*fields[i]->type());
1628 getTypePointer()->setQualifier(resultQualifier);
1629 return;
1630 }
1631 case EOpIndexDirectInterfaceBlock:
1632 {
1633 const TFieldList &fields = mLeft->getType().getInterfaceBlock()->fields();
1634 const int i = mRight->getAsConstantUnion()->getIConst(0);
1635 setType(*fields[i]->type());
1636 getTypePointer()->setQualifier(resultQualifier);
1637 return;
1638 }
1639 default:
1640 break;
1641 }
1642
1643 ASSERT(mLeft->isArray() == mRight->isArray());
1644
1645 // The result gets promoted to the highest precision.
1646 TPrecision higherPrecision = GetHigherPrecision(mLeft->getPrecision(), mRight->getPrecision());
1647 getTypePointer()->setPrecision(higherPrecision);
1648
1649 const int nominalSize = std::max(mLeft->getNominalSize(), mRight->getNominalSize());
1650
1651 //
1652 // All scalars or structs. Code after this test assumes this case is removed!
1653 //
1654 if (nominalSize == 1)
1655 {
1656 switch (mOp)
1657 {
1658 //
1659 // Promote to conditional
1660 //
1661 case EOpEqual:
1662 case EOpNotEqual:
1663 case EOpLessThan:
1664 case EOpGreaterThan:
1665 case EOpLessThanEqual:
1666 case EOpGreaterThanEqual:
1667 setType(TType(EbtBool, EbpUndefined, resultQualifier));
1668 break;
1669
1670 //
1671 // And and Or operate on conditionals
1672 //
1673 case EOpLogicalAnd:
1674 case EOpLogicalXor:
1675 case EOpLogicalOr:
1676 ASSERT(mLeft->getBasicType() == EbtBool && mRight->getBasicType() == EbtBool);
1677 setType(TType(EbtBool, EbpUndefined, resultQualifier));
1678 break;
1679
1680 default:
1681 break;
1682 }
1683 return;
1684 }
1685
1686 // If we reach here, at least one of the operands is vector or matrix.
1687 // The other operand could be a scalar, vector, or matrix.
1688 TBasicType basicType = mLeft->getBasicType();
1689
1690 switch (mOp)
1691 {
1692 case EOpMul:
1693 break;
1694 case EOpMatrixTimesScalar:
1695 if (mRight->isMatrix())
1696 {
1697 setType(TType(basicType, higherPrecision, resultQualifier,
1698 static_cast<unsigned char>(mRight->getCols()),
1699 static_cast<unsigned char>(mRight->getRows())));
1700 }
1701 break;
1702 case EOpMatrixTimesVector:
1703 setType(TType(basicType, higherPrecision, resultQualifier,
1704 static_cast<unsigned char>(mLeft->getRows()), 1));
1705 break;
1706 case EOpMatrixTimesMatrix:
1707 setType(TType(basicType, higherPrecision, resultQualifier,
1708 static_cast<unsigned char>(mRight->getCols()),
1709 static_cast<unsigned char>(mLeft->getRows())));
1710 break;
1711 case EOpVectorTimesScalar:
1712 setType(TType(basicType, higherPrecision, resultQualifier,
1713 static_cast<unsigned char>(nominalSize), 1));
1714 break;
1715 case EOpVectorTimesMatrix:
1716 setType(TType(basicType, higherPrecision, resultQualifier,
1717 static_cast<unsigned char>(mRight->getCols()), 1));
1718 break;
1719 case EOpMulAssign:
1720 case EOpVectorTimesScalarAssign:
1721 case EOpVectorTimesMatrixAssign:
1722 case EOpMatrixTimesScalarAssign:
1723 case EOpMatrixTimesMatrixAssign:
1724 ASSERT(mOp == GetMulAssignOpBasedOnOperands(mLeft->getType(), mRight->getType()));
1725 break;
1726 case EOpAssign:
1727 case EOpInitialize:
1728 ASSERT((mLeft->getNominalSize() == mRight->getNominalSize()) &&
1729 (mLeft->getSecondarySize() == mRight->getSecondarySize()));
1730 break;
1731 case EOpAdd:
1732 case EOpSub:
1733 case EOpDiv:
1734 case EOpIMod:
1735 case EOpBitShiftLeft:
1736 case EOpBitShiftRight:
1737 case EOpBitwiseAnd:
1738 case EOpBitwiseXor:
1739 case EOpBitwiseOr:
1740 case EOpAddAssign:
1741 case EOpSubAssign:
1742 case EOpDivAssign:
1743 case EOpIModAssign:
1744 case EOpBitShiftLeftAssign:
1745 case EOpBitShiftRightAssign:
1746 case EOpBitwiseAndAssign:
1747 case EOpBitwiseXorAssign:
1748 case EOpBitwiseOrAssign:
1749 {
1750 const int secondarySize =
1751 std::max(mLeft->getSecondarySize(), mRight->getSecondarySize());
1752 setType(TType(basicType, higherPrecision, resultQualifier,
1753 static_cast<unsigned char>(nominalSize),
1754 static_cast<unsigned char>(secondarySize)));
1755 ASSERT(!mLeft->isArray() && !mRight->isArray());
1756 break;
1757 }
1758 case EOpEqual:
1759 case EOpNotEqual:
1760 case EOpLessThan:
1761 case EOpGreaterThan:
1762 case EOpLessThanEqual:
1763 case EOpGreaterThanEqual:
1764 ASSERT((mLeft->getNominalSize() == mRight->getNominalSize()) &&
1765 (mLeft->getSecondarySize() == mRight->getSecondarySize()));
1766 setType(TType(EbtBool, EbpUndefined, resultQualifier));
1767 break;
1768
1769 case EOpIndexDirect:
1770 case EOpIndexIndirect:
1771 case EOpIndexDirectInterfaceBlock:
1772 case EOpIndexDirectStruct:
1773 // These ops should be already fully handled.
1774 UNREACHABLE();
1775 break;
1776 default:
1777 UNREACHABLE();
1778 break;
1779 }
1780}

1782bool TIntermConstantUnion::hasConstantValue() const
1783{
1784 return true;
1785}
1786
1787const TConstantUnion *TIntermConstantUnion::getConstantValue() const
1788{
1789 return mUnionArrayPointer;
1790}
1791
1792const TConstantUnion *TIntermConstantUnion::FoldIndexing(const TType &type,
1793 const TConstantUnion *constArray,
1794 int index)
1795{
1796 if (type.isArray())
1797 {
1798 ASSERT(index < static_cast<int>(type.getOutermostArraySize()));
1799 TType arrayElementType(type);
1800 arrayElementType.toArrayElementType();
1801 size_t arrayElementSize = arrayElementType.getObjectSize();
1802 return &constArray[arrayElementSize * index];
1803 }
1804 else if (type.isMatrix())
1805 {
1806 ASSERT(index < type.getCols());
1807 int size = type.getRows();
1808 return &constArray[size * index];
1809 }
1810 else if (type.isVector())
1811 {
1812 ASSERT(index < type.getNominalSize());
1813 return &constArray[index];
1814 }
1815 else
1816 {
1817 UNREACHABLE();
1818 return nullptr;
1819 }
1820}
1821
1822TIntermTyped *TIntermSwizzle::fold(TDiagnostics * /* diagnostics */)
1823{
1824 TIntermSwizzle *operandSwizzle = mOperand->getAsSwizzleNode();
1825 if (operandSwizzle)
1826 {
1827 // We need to fold the two swizzles into one, so that repeated swizzling can't cause stack
1828 // overflow in ParseContext::checkCanBeLValue().
1829 bool hadDuplicateOffsets = operandSwizzle->hasDuplicateOffsets();
1830 TVector<int> foldedOffsets;
1831 for (int offset : mSwizzleOffsets)
1832 {
1833 // Offset should already be validated.
1834 ASSERT(static_cast<size_t>(offset) < operandSwizzle->mSwizzleOffsets.size());
1835 foldedOffsets.push_back(operandSwizzle->mSwizzleOffsets[offset]);
1836 }
1837 operandSwizzle->mSwizzleOffsets = foldedOffsets;
1838 operandSwizzle->setType(getType());
1839 operandSwizzle->setHasFoldedDuplicateOffsets(hadDuplicateOffsets);
1840 return operandSwizzle;
1841 }
1842 TIntermConstantUnion *operandConstant = mOperand->getAsConstantUnion();
1843 if (operandConstant == nullptr)
1844 {
1845 return this;
1846 }
1847
1848 TConstantUnion *constArray = new TConstantUnion[mSwizzleOffsets.size()];
1849 for (size_t i = 0; i < mSwizzleOffsets.size(); ++i)
1850 {
1851 constArray[i] = *TIntermConstantUnion::FoldIndexing(
1852 operandConstant->getType(), operandConstant->getConstantValue(), mSwizzleOffsets.at(i));
1853 }
1854 return CreateFoldedNode(constArray, this);
1855}
1856
1857TIntermTyped *TIntermBinary::fold(TDiagnostics *diagnostics)
1858{
1859 const TConstantUnion *rightConstant = mRight->getConstantValue();
1860 switch (mOp)
1861 {
1862 case EOpComma:
1863 {
1864 if (mLeft->hasSideEffects())
1865 {
1866 return this;
1867 }
1868 return mRight;
1869 }
1870 case EOpIndexDirect:
1871 case EOpIndexDirectStruct:
1872 {
1873 if (rightConstant == nullptr)
1874 {
1875 return this;
1876 }
1877 size_t index = static_cast<size_t>(rightConstant->getIConst());
1878 TIntermAggregate *leftAggregate = mLeft->getAsAggregate();
1879 if (leftAggregate && leftAggregate->isConstructor() && leftAggregate->isArray() &&
1880 !leftAggregate->hasSideEffects())
1881 {
1882 ASSERT(index < leftAggregate->getSequence()->size());
1883 // This transformation can't add complexity as we're eliminating the constructor
1884 // entirely.
1885 return leftAggregate->getSequence()->at(index)->getAsTyped();
1886 }
1887
1888 // If the indexed value is already a constant union, we can't increase duplication of
1889 // data by folding the indexing. Also fold the node in case it's generally beneficial to
1890 // replace this type of node with a constant union even if that would mean duplicating
1891 // data.
1892 if (mLeft->getAsConstantUnion() || getType().canReplaceWithConstantUnion())
1893 {
1894 const TConstantUnion *constantValue = getConstantValue();
1895 if (constantValue == nullptr)
1896 {
1897 return this;
1898 }
1899 return CreateFoldedNode(constantValue, this);
1900 }
1901 return this;
1902 }
1903 case EOpIndexIndirect:
1904 case EOpIndexDirectInterfaceBlock:
1905 case EOpInitialize:
1906 // Can never be constant folded.
1907 return this;
1908 default:
1909 {
1910 if (rightConstant == nullptr)
1911 {
1912 return this;
1913 }
1914 const TConstantUnion *leftConstant = mLeft->getConstantValue();
1915 if (leftConstant == nullptr)
1916 {
1917 return this;
1918 }
1919 const TConstantUnion *constArray =
1920 TIntermConstantUnion::FoldBinary(mOp, leftConstant, mLeft->getType(), rightConstant,
1921 mRight->getType(), diagnostics, mLeft->getLine());
1922 if (!constArray)
1923 {
1924 return this;
1925 }
1926 return CreateFoldedNode(constArray, this);
1927 }
1928 }
1929}
1930
1931bool TIntermBinary::hasConstantValue() const
1932{
1933 switch (mOp)
1934 {
1935 case EOpIndexDirect:
1936 case EOpIndexDirectStruct:
1937 {
1938 if (mLeft->hasConstantValue() && mRight->hasConstantValue())
1939 {
1940 return true;
1941 }
1942 break;
1943 }
1944 default:
1945 break;
1946 }
1947 return false;
1948}
1949
1950const TConstantUnion *TIntermBinary::getConstantValue() const
1951{
1952 if (!hasConstantValue())
1953 {
1954 return nullptr;
1955 }
1956
1957 const TConstantUnion *leftConstantValue = mLeft->getConstantValue();
1958 int index = mRight->getConstantValue()->getIConst();
1959 const TConstantUnion *constIndexingResult = nullptr;
1960 if (mOp == EOpIndexDirect)
1961 {
1962 constIndexingResult =
1963 TIntermConstantUnion::FoldIndexing(mLeft->getType(), leftConstantValue, index);
1964 }
1965 else
1966 {
1967 ASSERT(mOp == EOpIndexDirectStruct);
1968 const TFieldList &fields = mLeft->getType().getStruct()->fields();
1969
1970 size_t previousFieldsSize = 0;
1971 for (int i = 0; i < index; ++i)
1972 {
1973 previousFieldsSize += fields[i]->type()->getObjectSize();
1974 }
1975 constIndexingResult = leftConstantValue + previousFieldsSize;
1976 }
1977 return constIndexingResult;
1978}
1979
1980const ImmutableString &TIntermBinary::getIndexStructFieldName() const
1981{
1982 ASSERT(mOp == EOpIndexDirectStruct);
1983
1984 const TType &lhsType = mLeft->getType();
1985 const TStructure *structure = lhsType.getStruct();
1986 const int index = mRight->getAsConstantUnion()->getIConst(0);
1987
1988 return structure->fields()[index]->name();
1989}
1990
1991TIntermTyped *TIntermUnary::fold(TDiagnostics *diagnostics)
1992{
1993 TConstantUnion *constArray = nullptr;
1994
1995 if (mOp == EOpArrayLength)
1996 {
1997 // The size of runtime-sized arrays may only be determined at runtime.
1998 if (mOperand->hasSideEffects() || mOperand->getType().isUnsizedArray())
1999 {
2000 return this;
2001 }
2002 constArray = new TConstantUnion[1];
2003 constArray->setIConst(mOperand->getOutermostArraySize());
2004 }
2005 else
2006 {
2007 TIntermConstantUnion *operandConstant = mOperand->getAsConstantUnion();
2008 if (operandConstant == nullptr)
2009 {
2010 return this;
2011 }
2012
2013 switch (mOp)
2014 {
2015 case EOpAny:
2016 case EOpAll:
2017 case EOpLength:
2018 case EOpTranspose:
2019 case EOpDeterminant:
2020 case EOpInverse:
2021 case EOpPackSnorm2x16:
2022 case EOpUnpackSnorm2x16:
2023 case EOpPackUnorm2x16:
2024 case EOpUnpackUnorm2x16:
2025 case EOpPackHalf2x16:
2026 case EOpUnpackHalf2x16:
2027 case EOpPackUnorm4x8:
2028 case EOpPackSnorm4x8:
2029 case EOpUnpackUnorm4x8:
2030 case EOpUnpackSnorm4x8:
2031 constArray = operandConstant->foldUnaryNonComponentWise(mOp);
2032 break;
2033 default:
2034 constArray = operandConstant->foldUnaryComponentWise(mOp, diagnostics);
2035 break;
2036 }
2037 }
2038 if (constArray == nullptr)
2039 {
2040 return this;
2041 }
2042 return CreateFoldedNode(constArray, this);
2043}
2044
2045TIntermTyped *TIntermAggregate::fold(TDiagnostics *diagnostics)
2046{
2047 // Make sure that all params are constant before actual constant folding.
2048 for (auto *param : *getSequence())
2049 {
2050 if (param->getAsConstantUnion() == nullptr)
2051 {
2052 return this;
2053 }
2054 }
2055 const TConstantUnion *constArray = nullptr;
2056 if (isConstructor())
2057 {
2058 if (mType.canReplaceWithConstantUnion())
2059 {
2060 constArray = getConstantValue();
2061 if (constArray && mType.getBasicType() == EbtUInt)
2062 {
2063 // Check if we converted a negative float to uint and issue a warning in that case.
2064 size_t sizeRemaining = mType.getObjectSize();
2065 for (TIntermNode *arg : mArguments)
2066 {
2067 TIntermTyped *typedArg = arg->getAsTyped();
2068 if (typedArg->getBasicType() == EbtFloat)
2069 {
2070 const TConstantUnion *argValue = typedArg->getConstantValue();
2071 size_t castSize =
2072 std::min(typedArg->getType().getObjectSize(), sizeRemaining);
2073 for (size_t i = 0; i < castSize; ++i)
2074 {
2075 if (argValue[i].getFConst() < 0.0f)
2076 {
2077 // ESSL 3.00.6 section 5.4.1.
2078 diagnostics->warning(
2079 mLine, "casting a negative float to uint is undefined",
2080 mType.getBuiltInTypeNameString());
2081 }
2082 }
2083 }
2084 sizeRemaining -= typedArg->getType().getObjectSize();
2085 }
2086 }
2087 }
2088 }
2089 else if (CanFoldAggregateBuiltInOp(mOp))
2090 {
2091 constArray = TIntermConstantUnion::FoldAggregateBuiltIn(this, diagnostics);
2092 }
2093 if (constArray == nullptr)
2094 {
2095 return this;
2096 }
2097 return CreateFoldedNode(constArray, this);
2098}
2099
2100//
2101// The fold functions see if an operation on a constant can be done in place,
2102// without generating run-time code.
2103//
2104// Returns the constant value to keep using or nullptr.
2105//
2106const TConstantUnion *TIntermConstantUnion::FoldBinary(TOperator op,
2107 const TConstantUnion *leftArray,
2108 const TType &leftType,
2109 const TConstantUnion *rightArray,
2110 const TType &rightType,
2111 TDiagnostics *diagnostics,
2112 const TSourceLoc &line)
2113{
2114 ASSERT(leftArray && rightArray);
2115
2116 size_t objectSize = leftType.getObjectSize();
2117
2118 // for a case like float f = vec4(2, 3, 4, 5) + 1.2;
2119 if (rightType.getObjectSize() == 1 && objectSize > 1)
2120 {
2121 rightArray = Vectorize(*rightArray, objectSize);
2122 }
2123 else if (rightType.getObjectSize() > 1 && objectSize == 1)
2124 {
2125 // for a case like float f = 1.2 + vec4(2, 3, 4, 5);
2126 leftArray = Vectorize(*leftArray, rightType.getObjectSize());
2127 objectSize = rightType.getObjectSize();
2128 }
2129
2130 TConstantUnion *resultArray = nullptr;
2131
2132 switch (op)
2133 {
2134 case EOpAdd:
2135 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2136 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2137 resultArray[i] =
2138 TConstantUnion::add(leftArray[i], rightArray[i], diagnostics, line);
2139 break;
2140 case EOpSub:
2141 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2142 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2143 resultArray[i] =
2144 TConstantUnion::sub(leftArray[i], rightArray[i], diagnostics, line);
2145 break;
2146
2147 case EOpMul:
2148 case EOpVectorTimesScalar:
2149 case EOpMatrixTimesScalar:
2150 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2151 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2152 resultArray[i] =
2153 TConstantUnion::mul(leftArray[i], rightArray[i], diagnostics, line);
2154 break;
2155
2156 case EOpMatrixTimesMatrix:
2157 {
2158 // TODO(jmadll): This code should check for overflows.
2159 ASSERT(leftType.getBasicType() == EbtFloat && rightType.getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2160
2161 const int leftCols = leftType.getCols();
2162 const int leftRows = leftType.getRows();
2163 const int rightCols = rightType.getCols();
2164 const int rightRows = rightType.getRows();
2165 const int resultCols = rightCols;
2166 const int resultRows = leftRows;
2167
2168 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[resultCols * resultRows];
2169 for (int row = 0; row < resultRows; row++)
2170 {
2171 for (int column = 0; column < resultCols; column++)
2172 {
2173 resultArray[resultRows * column + row].setFConst(0.0f);
2174 for (int i = 0; i < leftCols; i++)
2175 {
2176 resultArray[resultRows * column + row].setFConst(
2177 resultArray[resultRows * column + row].getFConst() +
2178 leftArray[i * leftRows + row].getFConst() *
2179 rightArray[column * rightRows + i].getFConst());
2180 }
2181 }
2182 }
2183 }
2184 break;
2185
2186 case EOpDiv:
2187 case EOpIMod:
2188 {
2189 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2190 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2191 {
2192 if (IsFloatDivision(leftType.getBasicType(), rightType.getBasicType()))
2193 {
2194 // Float division requested, possibly with implicit conversion
2195 ASSERT(op == EOpDiv);
2196 float dividend = leftArray[i].getFConst();
2197 float divisor = rightArray[i].getFConst();
2198
2199 if (divisor == 0.0f)
2200 {
2201 if (dividend == 0.0f)
2202 {
2203 diagnostics->warning(line,
2204 "Zero divided by zero during constant "
2205 "folding generated NaN",
2206 "/");
2207 resultArray[i].setFConst(std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN());
2208 }
2209 else
2210 {
2211 diagnostics->warning(line, "Divide by zero during constant folding",
2212 "/");
2213 bool negativeResult = std::signbit(dividend) != std::signbit(divisor);
2214 resultArray[i].setFConst(negativeResult
2215 ? -std::numeric_limits<float>::infinity()
2216 : std::numeric_limits<float>::infinity());
2217 }
2218 }
2219 else if (gl::isInf(dividend) && gl::isInf(divisor))
2220 {
2221 diagnostics->warning(line,
2222 "Infinity divided by infinity during constant "
2223 "folding generated NaN",
2224 "/");
2225 resultArray[i].setFConst(std::numeric_limits<float>::quiet_NaN());
2226 }
2227 else
2228 {
2229 float result = dividend / divisor;
2230 if (!gl::isInf(dividend) && gl::isInf(result))
2231 {
2232 diagnostics->warning(
2233 line, "Constant folded division overflowed to infinity", "/");
2234 }
2235 resultArray[i].setFConst(result);
2236 }
2237 }
2238 else
2239 {
2240 // Types are either both int or both uint
2241 switch (leftType.getBasicType())
2242 {
2243 case EbtInt:
2244 {
2245 if (rightArray[i] == 0)
2246 {
2247 diagnostics->warning(
2248 line, "Divide by zero error during constant folding", "/");
2249 resultArray[i].setIConst(INT_MAX);
2250 }
2251 else
2252 {
2253 int lhs = leftArray[i].getIConst();
2254 int divisor = rightArray[i].getIConst();
2255 if (op == EOpDiv)
2256 {
2257 // Check for the special case where the minimum
2258 // representable number is divided by -1. If left alone this
2259 // leads to integer overflow in C++. ESSL 3.00.6
2260 // section 4.1.3 Integers: "However, for the case where the
2261 // minimum representable value is divided by -1, it is
2262 // allowed to return either the minimum representable value
2263 // or the maximum representable value."
2264 if (lhs == -0x7fffffff - 1 && divisor == -1)
2265 {
2266 resultArray[i].setIConst(0x7fffffff);
2267 }
2268 else
2269 {
2270 resultArray[i].setIConst(lhs / divisor);
2271 }
2272 }
2273 else
2274 {
2275 ASSERT(op == EOpIMod);
2276 if (lhs < 0 || divisor < 0)
2277 {
2278 // ESSL 3.00.6 section 5.9: Results of modulus are
2279 // undefined when either one of the operands is
2280 // negative.
2281 diagnostics->warning(line,
2282 "Negative modulus operator operand "
2283 "encountered during constant folding. "
2284 "Results are undefined.",
2285 "%");
2286 resultArray[i].setIConst(0);
2287 }
2288 else
2289 {
2290 resultArray[i].setIConst(lhs % divisor);
2291 }
2292 }
2293 }
2294 break;
2295 }
2296 case EbtUInt:
2297 {
2298 if (rightArray[i] == 0)
2299 {
2300 diagnostics->warning(
2301 line, "Divide by zero error during constant folding", "/");
2302 resultArray[i].setUConst(UINT_MAX);
2303 }
2304 else
2305 {
2306 if (op == EOpDiv)
2307 {
2308 resultArray[i].setUConst(leftArray[i].getUConst() /
2309 rightArray[i].getUConst());
2310 }
2311 else
2312 {
2313 ASSERT(op == EOpIMod);
2314 resultArray[i].setUConst(leftArray[i].getUConst() %
2315 rightArray[i].getUConst());
2316 }
2317 }
2318 break;
2319 }
2320 default:
2321 UNREACHABLE();
2322 return nullptr;
2323 }
2324 }
2325 }
2326 }
2327 break;
2328
2329 case EOpMatrixTimesVector:
2330 {
2331 // TODO(jmadll): This code should check for overflows.
2332 ASSERT(rightType.getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2333
2334 const int matrixCols = leftType.getCols();
2335 const int matrixRows = leftType.getRows();
2336
2337 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[matrixRows];
2338
2339 for (int matrixRow = 0; matrixRow < matrixRows; matrixRow++)
2340 {
2341 resultArray[matrixRow].setFConst(0.0f);
2342 for (int col = 0; col < matrixCols; col++)
2343 {
2344 resultArray[matrixRow].setFConst(
2345 resultArray[matrixRow].getFConst() +
2346 leftArray[col * matrixRows + matrixRow].getFConst() *
2347 rightArray[col].getFConst());
2348 }
2349 }
2350 }
2351 break;
2352
2353 case EOpVectorTimesMatrix:
2354 {
2355 // TODO(jmadll): This code should check for overflows.
2356 ASSERT(leftType.getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2357
2358 const int matrixCols = rightType.getCols();
2359 const int matrixRows = rightType.getRows();
2360
2361 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[matrixCols];
2362
2363 for (int matrixCol = 0; matrixCol < matrixCols; matrixCol++)
2364 {
2365 resultArray[matrixCol].setFConst(0.0f);
2366 for (int matrixRow = 0; matrixRow < matrixRows; matrixRow++)
2367 {
2368 resultArray[matrixCol].setFConst(
2369 resultArray[matrixCol].getFConst() +
2370 leftArray[matrixRow].getFConst() *
2371 rightArray[matrixCol * matrixRows + matrixRow].getFConst());
2372 }
2373 }
2374 }
2375 break;
2376
2377 case EOpLogicalAnd:
2378 {
2379 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2380 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2381 {
2382 resultArray[i] = leftArray[i] && rightArray[i];
2383 }
2384 }
2385 break;
2386
2387 case EOpLogicalOr:
2388 {
2389 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2390 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2391 {
2392 resultArray[i] = leftArray[i] || rightArray[i];
2393 }
2394 }
2395 break;
2396
2397 case EOpLogicalXor:
2398 {
2399 ASSERT(leftType.getBasicType() == EbtBool);
2400 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2401 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2402 {
2403 resultArray[i].setBConst(leftArray[i] != rightArray[i]);
2404 }
2405 }
2406 break;
2407
2408 case EOpBitwiseAnd:
2409 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2410 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2411 resultArray[i] = leftArray[i] & rightArray[i];
2412 break;
2413 case EOpBitwiseXor:
2414 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2415 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2416 resultArray[i] = leftArray[i] ^ rightArray[i];
2417 break;
2418 case EOpBitwiseOr:
2419 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2420 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2421 resultArray[i] = leftArray[i] | rightArray[i];
2422 break;
2423 case EOpBitShiftLeft:
2424 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2425 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2426 resultArray[i] =
2427 TConstantUnion::lshift(leftArray[i], rightArray[i], diagnostics, line);
2428 break;
2429 case EOpBitShiftRight:
2430 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2431 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2432 resultArray[i] =
2433 TConstantUnion::rshift(leftArray[i], rightArray[i], diagnostics, line);
2434 break;
2435
2436 case EOpLessThan:
2437 ASSERT(objectSize == 1);
2438 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[1];
2439 resultArray->setBConst(*leftArray < *rightArray);
2440 break;
2441
2442 case EOpGreaterThan:
2443 ASSERT(objectSize == 1);
2444 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[1];
2445 resultArray->setBConst(*leftArray > *rightArray);
2446 break;
2447
2448 case EOpLessThanEqual:
2449 ASSERT(objectSize == 1);
2450 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[1];
2451 resultArray->setBConst(!(*leftArray > *rightArray));
2452 break;
2453
2454 case EOpGreaterThanEqual:
2455 ASSERT(objectSize == 1);
2456 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[1];
2457 resultArray->setBConst(!(*leftArray < *rightArray));
2458 break;
2459
2460 case EOpEqual:
2461 case EOpNotEqual:
2462 {
2463 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[1];
2464 bool equal = true;
2465 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2466 {
2467 if (leftArray[i] != rightArray[i])
2468 {
2469 equal = false;
2470 break; // break out of for loop
2471 }
2472 }
2473 if (op == EOpEqual)
2474 {
2475 resultArray->setBConst(equal);
2476 }
2477 else
2478 {
2479 resultArray->setBConst(!equal);
2480 }
2481 }
2482 break;
2483
2484 default:
2485 UNREACHABLE();
2486 return nullptr;
2487 }
2488 return resultArray;
2489}

2491// The fold functions do operations on a constant at GLSL compile time, without generating run-time
2492// code. Returns the constant value to keep using. Nullptr should not be returned.
2493TConstantUnion *TIntermConstantUnion::foldUnaryNonComponentWise(TOperator op)
2494{
2495 // Do operations where the return type may have a different number of components compared to the
2496 // operand type.
2497
2498 const TConstantUnion *operandArray = getConstantValue();
2499 ASSERT(operandArray);
2500
2501 size_t objectSize = getType().getObjectSize();
2502 TConstantUnion *resultArray = nullptr;
2503 switch (op)
2504 {
2505 case EOpAny:
2506 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtBool);
2507 resultArray = new TConstantUnion();
2508 resultArray->setBConst(false);
2509 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2510 {
2511 if (operandArray[i].getBConst())
2512 {
2513 resultArray->setBConst(true);
2514 break;
2515 }
2516 }
2517 break;
2518
2519 case EOpAll:
2520 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtBool);
2521 resultArray = new TConstantUnion();
2522 resultArray->setBConst(true);
2523 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2524 {
2525 if (!operandArray[i].getBConst())
2526 {
2527 resultArray->setBConst(false);
2528 break;
2529 }
2530 }
2531 break;
2532
2533 case EOpLength:
2534 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2535 resultArray = new TConstantUnion();
2536 resultArray->setFConst(VectorLength(operandArray, objectSize));
2537 break;
2538
2539 case EOpTranspose:
2540 {
2541 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2542 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2543 angle::Matrix<float> result =
2544 GetMatrix(operandArray, getType().getRows(), getType().getCols()).transpose();
2545 SetUnionArrayFromMatrix(result, resultArray);
2546 break;
2547 }
2548
2549 case EOpDeterminant:
2550 {
2551 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2552 unsigned int size = getType().getNominalSize();
2553 ASSERT(size >= 2 && size <= 4);
2554 resultArray = new TConstantUnion();
2555 resultArray->setFConst(GetMatrix(operandArray, size).determinant());
2556 break;
2557 }
2558
2559 case EOpInverse:
2560 {
2561 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2562 unsigned int size = getType().getNominalSize();
2563 ASSERT(size >= 2 && size <= 4);
2564 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2565 angle::Matrix<float> result = GetMatrix(operandArray, size).inverse();
2566 SetUnionArrayFromMatrix(result, resultArray);
2567 break;
2568 }
2569
2570 case EOpPackSnorm2x16:
2571 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2572 ASSERT(getType().getNominalSize() == 2);
2573 resultArray = new TConstantUnion();
2574 resultArray->setUConst(
2575 gl::packSnorm2x16(operandArray[0].getFConst(), operandArray[1].getFConst()));
2576 break;
2577
2578 case EOpUnpackSnorm2x16:
2579 {
2580 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
2581 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[2];
2582 float f1, f2;
2583 gl::unpackSnorm2x16(operandArray[0].getUConst(), &f1, &f2);
2584 resultArray[0].setFConst(f1);
2585 resultArray[1].setFConst(f2);
2586 break;
2587 }
2588
2589 case EOpPackUnorm2x16:
2590 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2591 ASSERT(getType().getNominalSize() == 2);
2592 resultArray = new TConstantUnion();
2593 resultArray->setUConst(
2594 gl::packUnorm2x16(operandArray[0].getFConst(), operandArray[1].getFConst()));
2595 break;
2596
2597 case EOpUnpackUnorm2x16:
2598 {
2599 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
2600 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[2];
2601 float f1, f2;
2602 gl::unpackUnorm2x16(operandArray[0].getUConst(), &f1, &f2);
2603 resultArray[0].setFConst(f1);
2604 resultArray[1].setFConst(f2);
2605 break;
2606 }
2607
2608 case EOpPackHalf2x16:
2609 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2610 ASSERT(getType().getNominalSize() == 2);
2611 resultArray = new TConstantUnion();
2612 resultArray->setUConst(
2613 gl::packHalf2x16(operandArray[0].getFConst(), operandArray[1].getFConst()));
2614 break;
2615
2616 case EOpUnpackHalf2x16:
2617 {
2618 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
2619 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[2];
2620 float f1, f2;
2621 gl::unpackHalf2x16(operandArray[0].getUConst(), &f1, &f2);
2622 resultArray[0].setFConst(f1);
2623 resultArray[1].setFConst(f2);
2624 break;
2625 }
2626
2627 case EOpPackUnorm4x8:
2628 {
2629 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2630 resultArray = new TConstantUnion();
2631 resultArray->setUConst(
2632 gl::PackUnorm4x8(operandArray[0].getFConst(), operandArray[1].getFConst(),
2633 operandArray[2].getFConst(), operandArray[3].getFConst()));
2634 break;
2635 }
2636 case EOpPackSnorm4x8:
2637 {
2638 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2639 resultArray = new TConstantUnion();
2640 resultArray->setUConst(
2641 gl::PackSnorm4x8(operandArray[0].getFConst(), operandArray[1].getFConst(),
2642 operandArray[2].getFConst(), operandArray[3].getFConst()));
2643 break;
2644 }
2645 case EOpUnpackUnorm4x8:
2646 {
2647 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
2648 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[4];
2649 float f[4];
2650 gl::UnpackUnorm4x8(operandArray[0].getUConst(), f);
2651 for (size_t i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
2652 {
2653 resultArray[i].setFConst(f[i]);
2654 }
2655 break;
2656 }
2657 case EOpUnpackSnorm4x8:
2658 {
2659 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
2660 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[4];
2661 float f[4];
2662 gl::UnpackSnorm4x8(operandArray[0].getUConst(), f);
2663 for (size_t i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
2664 {
2665 resultArray[i].setFConst(f[i]);
2666 }
2667 break;
2668 }
2669
2670 default:
2671 UNREACHABLE();
2672 break;
2673 }
2674
2675 return resultArray;
2676}
2677
2678TConstantUnion *TIntermConstantUnion::foldUnaryComponentWise(TOperator op,
2679 TDiagnostics *diagnostics)
2680{
2681 // Do unary operations where each component of the result is computed based on the corresponding
2682 // component of the operand. Also folds normalize, though the divisor in that case takes all
2683 // components into account.
2684
2685 const TConstantUnion *operandArray = getConstantValue();
2686 ASSERT(operandArray);
2687
2688 size_t objectSize = getType().getObjectSize();
2689
2690 TConstantUnion *resultArray = new TConstantUnion[objectSize];
2691 for (size_t i = 0; i < objectSize; i++)
2692 {
2693 switch (op)
2694 {
2695 case EOpNegative:
2696 switch (getType().getBasicType())
2697 {
2698 case EbtFloat:
2699 resultArray[i].setFConst(-operandArray[i].getFConst());
2700 break;
2701 case EbtInt:
2702 if (operandArray[i] == std::numeric_limits<int>::min())
2703 {
2704 // The minimum representable integer doesn't have a positive
2705 // counterpart, rather the negation overflows and in ESSL is supposed to
2706 // wrap back to the minimum representable integer. Make sure that we
2707 // don't actually let the negation overflow, which has undefined
2708 // behavior in C++.
2709 resultArray[i].setIConst(std::numeric_limits<int>::min());
2710 }
2711 else
2712 {
2713 resultArray[i].setIConst(-operandArray[i].getIConst());
2714 }
2715 break;
2716 case EbtUInt:
2717 if (operandArray[i] == 0x80000000u)
2718 {
2719 resultArray[i].setUConst(0x80000000u);
2720 }
2721 else
2722 {
2723 resultArray[i].setUConst(static_cast<unsigned int>(
2724 -static_cast<int>(operandArray[i].getUConst())));
2725 }
2726 break;
2727 default:
2728 UNREACHABLE();
2729 return nullptr;
2730 }
2731 break;
2732
2733 case EOpPositive:
2734 switch (getType().getBasicType())
2735 {
2736 case EbtFloat:
2737 resultArray[i].setFConst(operandArray[i].getFConst());
2738 break;
2739 case EbtInt:
2740 resultArray[i].setIConst(operandArray[i].getIConst());
2741 break;
2742 case EbtUInt:
2743 resultArray[i].setUConst(static_cast<unsigned int>(
2744 static_cast<int>(operandArray[i].getUConst())));
2745 break;
2746 default:
2747 UNREACHABLE();
2748 return nullptr;
2749 }
2750 break;
2751
2752 case EOpLogicalNot:
2753 switch (getType().getBasicType())
2754 {
2755 case EbtBool:
2756 resultArray[i].setBConst(!operandArray[i].getBConst());
2757 break;
2758 default:
2759 UNREACHABLE();
2760 return nullptr;
2761 }
2762 break;
2763
2764 case EOpBitwiseNot:
2765 switch (getType().getBasicType())
2766 {
2767 case EbtInt:
2768 resultArray[i].setIConst(~operandArray[i].getIConst());
2769 break;
2770 case EbtUInt:
2771 resultArray[i].setUConst(~operandArray[i].getUConst());
2772 break;
2773 default:
2774 UNREACHABLE();
2775 return nullptr;
2776 }
2777 break;
2778
2779 case EOpRadians:
2780 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2781 resultArray[i].setFConst(kDegreesToRadiansMultiplier * operandArray[i].getFConst());
2782 break;
2783
2784 case EOpDegrees:
2785 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2786 resultArray[i].setFConst(kRadiansToDegreesMultiplier * operandArray[i].getFConst());
2787 break;
2788
2789 case EOpSin:
2790 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &sinf, &resultArray[i]);
2791 break;
2792
2793 case EOpCos:
2794 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &cosf, &resultArray[i]);
2795 break;
2796
2797 case EOpTan:
2798 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &tanf, &resultArray[i]);
2799 break;
2800
2801 case EOpAsin:
2802 // For asin(x), results are undefined if |x| > 1, we are choosing to set result to
2803 // 0.
2804 if (fabsf(operandArray[i].getFConst()) > 1.0f)
2805 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(getLine(), op, getType().getBasicType(),
2806 diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
2807 else
2808 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &asinf, &resultArray[i]);
2809 break;
2810
2811 case EOpAcos:
2812 // For acos(x), results are undefined if |x| > 1, we are choosing to set result to
2813 // 0.
2814 if (fabsf(operandArray[i].getFConst()) > 1.0f)
2815 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(getLine(), op, getType().getBasicType(),
2816 diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
2817 else
2818 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &acosf, &resultArray[i]);
2819 break;
2820
2821 case EOpAtan:
2822 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &atanf, &resultArray[i]);
2823 break;
2824
2825 case EOpSinh:
2826 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &sinhf, &resultArray[i]);
2827 break;
2828
2829 case EOpCosh:
2830 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &coshf, &resultArray[i]);
2831 break;
2832
2833 case EOpTanh:
2834 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &tanhf, &resultArray[i]);
2835 break;
2836
2837 case EOpAsinh:
2838 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &asinhf, &resultArray[i]);
2839 break;
2840
2841 case EOpAcosh:
2842 // For acosh(x), results are undefined if x < 1, we are choosing to set result to 0.
2843 if (operandArray[i].getFConst() < 1.0f)
2844 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(getLine(), op, getType().getBasicType(),
2845 diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
2846 else
2847 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &acoshf, &resultArray[i]);
2848 break;
2849
2850 case EOpAtanh:
2851 // For atanh(x), results are undefined if |x| >= 1, we are choosing to set result to
2852 // 0.
2853 if (fabsf(operandArray[i].getFConst()) >= 1.0f)
2854 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(getLine(), op, getType().getBasicType(),
2855 diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
2856 else
2857 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &atanhf, &resultArray[i]);
2858 break;
2859
2860 case EOpAbs:
2861 switch (getType().getBasicType())
2862 {
2863 case EbtFloat:
2864 resultArray[i].setFConst(fabsf(operandArray[i].getFConst()));
2865 break;
2866 case EbtInt:
2867 resultArray[i].setIConst(abs(operandArray[i].getIConst()));
2868 break;
2869 default:
2870 UNREACHABLE();
2871 return nullptr;
2872 }
2873 break;
2874
2875 case EOpSign:
2876 switch (getType().getBasicType())
2877 {
2878 case EbtFloat:
2879 {
2880 float fConst = operandArray[i].getFConst();
2881 float fResult = 0.0f;
2882 if (fConst > 0.0f)
2883 fResult = 1.0f;
2884 else if (fConst < 0.0f)
2885 fResult = -1.0f;
2886 resultArray[i].setFConst(fResult);
2887 break;
2888 }
2889 case EbtInt:
2890 {
2891 int iConst = operandArray[i].getIConst();
2892 int iResult = 0;
2893 if (iConst > 0)
2894 iResult = 1;
2895 else if (iConst < 0)
2896 iResult = -1;
2897 resultArray[i].setIConst(iResult);
2898 break;
2899 }
2900 default:
2901 UNREACHABLE();
2902 return nullptr;
2903 }
2904 break;
2905
2906 case EOpFloor:
2907 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &floorf, &resultArray[i]);
2908 break;
2909
2910 case EOpTrunc:
2911 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &truncf, &resultArray[i]);
2912 break;
2913
2914 case EOpRound:
2915 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &roundf, &resultArray[i]);
2916 break;
2917
2918 case EOpRoundEven:
2919 {
2920 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2921 float x = operandArray[i].getFConst();
2922 float result;
2923 float fractPart = modff(x, &result);
2924 if (fabsf(fractPart) == 0.5f)
2925 result = 2.0f * roundf(x / 2.0f);
2926 else
2927 result = roundf(x);
2928 resultArray[i].setFConst(result);
2929 break;
2930 }
2931
2932 case EOpCeil:
2933 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &ceilf, &resultArray[i]);
2934 break;
2935
2936 case EOpFract:
2937 {
2938 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2939 float x = operandArray[i].getFConst();
2940 resultArray[i].setFConst(x - floorf(x));
2941 break;
2942 }
2943
2944 case EOpIsnan:
2945 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2946 resultArray[i].setBConst(gl::isNaN(operandArray[0].getFConst()));
2947 break;
2948
2949 case EOpIsinf:
2950 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2951 resultArray[i].setBConst(gl::isInf(operandArray[0].getFConst()));
2952 break;
2953
2954 case EOpFloatBitsToInt:
2955 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2956 resultArray[i].setIConst(gl::bitCast<int32_t>(operandArray[0].getFConst()));
2957 break;
2958
2959 case EOpFloatBitsToUint:
2960 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
2961 resultArray[i].setUConst(gl::bitCast<uint32_t>(operandArray[0].getFConst()));
2962 break;
2963
2964 case EOpIntBitsToFloat:
2965 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtInt);
2966 resultArray[i].setFConst(gl::bitCast<float>(operandArray[0].getIConst()));
2967 break;
2968
2969 case EOpUintBitsToFloat:
2970 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
2971 resultArray[i].setFConst(gl::bitCast<float>(operandArray[0].getUConst()));
2972 break;
2973
2974 case EOpExp:
2975 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &expf, &resultArray[i]);
2976 break;
2977
2978 case EOpLog:
2979 // For log(x), results are undefined if x <= 0, we are choosing to set result to 0.
2980 if (operandArray[i].getFConst() <= 0.0f)
2981 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(getLine(), op, getType().getBasicType(),
2982 diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
2983 else
2984 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &logf, &resultArray[i]);
2985 break;
2986
2987 case EOpExp2:
2988 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &exp2f, &resultArray[i]);
2989 break;
2990
2991 case EOpLog2:
2992 // For log2(x), results are undefined if x <= 0, we are choosing to set result to 0.
2993 // And log2f is not available on some plarforms like old android, so just using
2994 // log(x)/log(2) here.
2995 if (operandArray[i].getFConst() <= 0.0f)
2996 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(getLine(), op, getType().getBasicType(),
2997 diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
2998 else
2999 {
3000 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &logf, &resultArray[i]);
3001 resultArray[i].setFConst(resultArray[i].getFConst() / logf(2.0f));
3002 }
3003 break;
3004
3005 case EOpSqrt:
3006 // For sqrt(x), results are undefined if x < 0, we are choosing to set result to 0.
3007 if (operandArray[i].getFConst() < 0.0f)
3008 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(getLine(), op, getType().getBasicType(),
3009 diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
3010 else
3011 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &sqrtf, &resultArray[i]);
3012 break;
3013
3014 case EOpInversesqrt:
3015 // There is no stdlib built-in function equavalent for GLES built-in inversesqrt(),
3016 // so getting the square root first using builtin function sqrt() and then taking
3017 // its inverse.
3018 // Also, for inversesqrt(x), results are undefined if x <= 0, we are choosing to set
3019 // result to 0.
3020 if (operandArray[i].getFConst() <= 0.0f)
3021 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(getLine(), op, getType().getBasicType(),
3022 diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
3023 else
3024 {
3025 foldFloatTypeUnary(operandArray[i], &sqrtf, &resultArray[i]);
3026 resultArray[i].setFConst(1.0f / resultArray[i].getFConst());
3027 }
3028 break;
3029
3030 case EOpLogicalNotComponentWise:
3031 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtBool);
3032 resultArray[i].setBConst(!operandArray[i].getBConst());
3033 break;
3034
3035 case EOpNormalize:
3036 {
3037 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
3038 float x = operandArray[i].getFConst();
3039 float length = VectorLength(operandArray, objectSize);
3040 if (length != 0.0f)
3041 resultArray[i].setFConst(x / length);
3042 else
3043 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(getLine(), op, getType().getBasicType(),
3044 diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
3045 break;
3046 }
3047 case EOpBitfieldReverse:
3048 {
3049 uint32_t value;
3050 if (getType().getBasicType() == EbtInt)
3051 {
3052 value = static_cast<uint32_t>(operandArray[i].getIConst());
3053 }
3054 else
3055 {
3056 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
3057 value = operandArray[i].getUConst();
3058 }
3059 uint32_t result = gl::BitfieldReverse(value);
3060 if (getType().getBasicType() == EbtInt)
3061 {
3062 resultArray[i].setIConst(static_cast<int32_t>(result));
3063 }
3064 else
3065 {
3066 resultArray[i].setUConst(result);
3067 }
3068 break;
3069 }
3070 case EOpBitCount:
3071 {
3072 uint32_t value;
3073 if (getType().getBasicType() == EbtInt)
3074 {
3075 value = static_cast<uint32_t>(operandArray[i].getIConst());
3076 }
3077 else
3078 {
3079 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
3080 value = operandArray[i].getUConst();
3081 }
3082 int result = gl::BitCount(value);
3083 resultArray[i].setIConst(result);
3084 break;
3085 }
3086 case EOpFindLSB:
3087 {
3088 uint32_t value;
3089 if (getType().getBasicType() == EbtInt)
3090 {
3091 value = static_cast<uint32_t>(operandArray[i].getIConst());
3092 }
3093 else
3094 {
3095 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
3096 value = operandArray[i].getUConst();
3097 }
3098 resultArray[i].setIConst(gl::FindLSB(value));
3099 break;
3100 }
3101 case EOpFindMSB:
3102 {
3103 uint32_t value;
3104 if (getType().getBasicType() == EbtInt)
3105 {
3106 int intValue = operandArray[i].getIConst();
3107 value = static_cast<uint32_t>(intValue);
3108 if (intValue < 0)
3109 {
3110 // Look for zero instead of one in value. This also handles the intValue ==
3111 // -1 special case, where the return value needs to be -1.
3112 value = ~value;
3113 }
3114 }
3115 else
3116 {
3117 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
3118 value = operandArray[i].getUConst();
3119 }
3120 resultArray[i].setIConst(gl::FindMSB(value));
3121 break;
3122 }
3123 case EOpDFdx:
3124 case EOpDFdy:
3125 case EOpFwidth:
3126 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
3127 // Derivatives of constant arguments should be 0.
3128 resultArray[i].setFConst(0.0f);
3129 break;
3130
3131 default:
3132 return nullptr;
3133 }
3134 }
3135
3136 return resultArray;
3137}
3138
3139void TIntermConstantUnion::foldFloatTypeUnary(const TConstantUnion &parameter,
3140 FloatTypeUnaryFunc builtinFunc,
3141 TConstantUnion *result) const
3142{
3143 ASSERT(builtinFunc);
3144
3145 ASSERT(getType().getBasicType() == EbtFloat);
3146 result->setFConst(builtinFunc(parameter.getFConst()));
3147}

3149// static
3150TConstantUnion *TIntermConstantUnion::FoldAggregateBuiltIn(TIntermAggregate *aggregate,
3151 TDiagnostics *diagnostics)
3152{
3153 TOperator op = aggregate->getOp();
3154 TIntermSequence *arguments = aggregate->getSequence();
3155 unsigned int argsCount = static_cast<unsigned int>(arguments->size());
3156 std::vector<const TConstantUnion *> unionArrays(argsCount);
3157 std::vector<size_t> objectSizes(argsCount);
3158 size_t maxObjectSize = 0;
3159 TBasicType basicType = EbtVoid;
3160 TSourceLoc loc;
3161 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < argsCount; i++)
3162 {
3163 TIntermConstantUnion *argConstant = (*arguments)[i]->getAsConstantUnion();
3164 ASSERT(argConstant != nullptr); // Should be checked already.
3165
3166 if (i == 0)
3167 {
3168 basicType = argConstant->getType().getBasicType();
3169 loc = argConstant->getLine();
3170 }
3171 unionArrays[i] = argConstant->getConstantValue();
3172 objectSizes[i] = argConstant->getType().getObjectSize();
3173 if (objectSizes[i] > maxObjectSize)
3174 maxObjectSize = objectSizes[i];
3175 }
3176
3177 if (!(*arguments)[0]->getAsTyped()->isMatrix() && aggregate->getOp() != EOpOuterProduct)
3178 {
3179 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < argsCount; i++)
3180 if (objectSizes[i] != maxObjectSize)
3181 unionArrays[i] = Vectorize(*unionArrays[i], maxObjectSize);
3182 }
3183
3184 TConstantUnion *resultArray = nullptr;
3185
3186 switch (op)
3187 {
3188 case EOpAtan:
3189 {
3190 ASSERT(basicType == EbtFloat);
3191 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[maxObjectSize];
3192 for (size_t i = 0; i < maxObjectSize; i++)
3193 {
3194 float y = unionArrays[0][i].getFConst();
3195 float x = unionArrays[1][i].getFConst();
3196 // Results are undefined if x and y are both 0.
3197 if (x == 0.0f && y == 0.0f)
3198 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(loc, op, basicType, diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
3199 else
3200 resultArray[i].setFConst(atan2f(y, x));
3201 }
3202 break;
3203 }

3205 case EOpPow:
3206 {
3207 ASSERT(basicType == EbtFloat);

3209 for (size_t i = 0; i < maxObjectSize; i++)
3210 {
3211 float x = unionArrays[0][i].getFConst();
3212 float y = unionArrays[1][i].getFConst();
3213 // Results are undefined if x < 0.
3214 // Results are undefined if x = 0 and y <= 0.
3215 if (x < 0.0f)
3216 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(loc, op, basicType, diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
3217 else if (x == 0.0f && y <= 0.0f)
3218 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(loc, op, basicType, diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);

3238 case EOpMin:

3247 std::min(unionArrays[0][i].getFConst(), unionArrays[1][i].getFConst()));
3248 break;
3249 case EbtInt:
3250 resultArray[i].setIConst(
3251 std::min(unionArrays[0][i].getIConst(), unionArrays[1][i].getIConst()));
3252 break;
3253 case EbtUInt:
3254 resultArray[i].setUConst(
3255 std::min(unionArrays[0][i].getUConst(), unionArrays[1][i].getUConst()));

3274 std::max(unionArrays[0][i].getFConst(), unionArrays[1][i].getFConst()));
3275 break;
3276 case EbtInt:

3500 float y1 = unionArrays[1][1].getFConst();

3515 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[maxObjectSize];

3517 for (size_t i = 0; i < maxObjectSize; i++)
3518 {

3520 2.0f * dotProduct * unionArrays[1][i].getFConst();

3580 // Results are undefined if min > max.
3581 if (min > max)
3582 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(loc, op, basicType, diagnostics,
3583 &resultArray[i]);
3584 else
3585 resultArray[i].setIConst(gl::clamp(x, min, max));
3586 break;
3587 }
3588 case EbtUInt:
3589 {
3590 unsigned int x = unionArrays[0][i].getUConst();
3591 unsigned int min = unionArrays[1][i].getUConst();
3592 unsigned int max = unionArrays[2][i].getUConst();
3593 // Results are undefined if min > max.
3594 if (min > max)
3595 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(loc, op, basicType, diagnostics,
3596 &resultArray[i]);
3597 else
3598 resultArray[i].setUConst(gl::clamp(x, min, max));
3599 break;
3600 }

3602 UNREACHABLE();
3603 break;
3604 }

3607 }
3608
3609 case EOpMix:
3610 {
3611 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[maxObjectSize];
3612 for (size_t i = 0; i < maxObjectSize; i++)
3613 {
3614 TBasicType type = (*arguments)[2]->getAsTyped()->getType().getBasicType();
3615 if (type == EbtFloat)
3616 {
3617 ASSERT(basicType == EbtFloat);
3618 float x = unionArrays[0][i].getFConst();
3619 float y = unionArrays[1][i].getFConst();
3620
3621 // Returns the linear blend of x and y, i.e., x * (1 - a) + y * a.
3622 float a = unionArrays[2][i].getFConst();
3623 resultArray[i].setFConst(x * (1.0f - a) + y * a);
3624 }
3625 else // 3rd parameter is EbtBool
3626 {
3627 ASSERT(type == EbtBool);
3628 // Selects which vector each returned component comes from.
3629 // For a component of a that is false, the corresponding component of x is
3630 // returned.
3631 // For a component of a that is true, the corresponding component of y is
3632 // returned.
3633 bool a = unionArrays[2][i].getBConst();
3634 switch (basicType)
3635 {
3636 case EbtFloat:
3637 {
3638 float x = unionArrays[0][i].getFConst();
3639 float y = unionArrays[1][i].getFConst();
3640 resultArray[i].setFConst(a ? y : x);
3641 }
3642 break;
3643 case EbtInt:
3644 {
3645 int x = unionArrays[0][i].getIConst();
3646 int y = unionArrays[1][i].getIConst();
3647 resultArray[i].setIConst(a ? y : x);
3648 }
3649 break;
3650 case EbtUInt:
3651 {
3652 unsigned int x = unionArrays[0][i].getUConst();
3653 unsigned int y = unionArrays[1][i].getUConst();
3654 resultArray[i].setUConst(a ? y : x);
3655 }
3656 break;
3657 case EbtBool:
3658 {
3659 bool x = unionArrays[0][i].getBConst();
3660 bool y = unionArrays[1][i].getBConst();
3661 resultArray[i].setBConst(a ? y : x);
3662 }
3663 break;
3664 default:
3665 UNREACHABLE();
3666 break;
3667 }
3668 }
3669 }
3670 break;
3671 }
3672
3673 case EOpSmoothstep:
3674 {
3675 ASSERT(basicType == EbtFloat);
3676 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[maxObjectSize];
3677 for (size_t i = 0; i < maxObjectSize; i++)
3678 {
3679 float edge0 = unionArrays[0][i].getFConst();
3680 float edge1 = unionArrays[1][i].getFConst();
3681 float x = unionArrays[2][i].getFConst();
3682 // Results are undefined if edge0 >= edge1.
3683 if (edge0 >= edge1)
3684 {
3685 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(loc, op, basicType, diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
3686 }
3687 else
3688 {
3689 // Returns 0.0 if x <= edge0 and 1.0 if x >= edge1 and performs smooth
3690 // Hermite interpolation between 0 and 1 when edge0 < x < edge1.
3691 float t = gl::clamp((x - edge0) / (edge1 - edge0), 0.0f, 1.0f);
3692 resultArray[i].setFConst(t * t * (3.0f - 2.0f * t));
3693 }
3694 }
3695 break;
3696 }
3697
3698 case EOpFma:
3699 {
3700 ASSERT(basicType == EbtFloat);
3701 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[maxObjectSize];
3702 for (size_t i = 0; i < maxObjectSize; i++)
3703 {
3704 float a = unionArrays[0][i].getFConst();
3705 float b = unionArrays[1][i].getFConst();
3706 float c = unionArrays[2][i].getFConst();
3707
3708 // Returns a * b + c.
3709 resultArray[i].setFConst(a * b + c);
3710 }
3711 break;
3712 }
3713
3714 case EOpLdexp:
3715 {
3716 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[maxObjectSize];
3717 for (size_t i = 0; i < maxObjectSize; i++)
3718 {
3719 float x = unionArrays[0][i].getFConst();
3720 int exp = unionArrays[1][i].getIConst();
3721 if (exp > 128)
3722 {
3723 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(loc, op, basicType, diagnostics, &resultArray[i]);
3724 }
3725 else
3726 {
3727 resultArray[i].setFConst(gl::Ldexp(x, exp));
3728 }
3729 }
3730 break;
3731 }
3732
3733 case EOpFaceforward:
3734 {
3735 ASSERT(basicType == EbtFloat);
3736 // genType faceforward(genType N, genType I, genType Nref) :
3737 // If dot(Nref, I) < 0 return N, otherwise return -N.
3738 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[maxObjectSize];
3739 float dotProduct = VectorDotProduct(unionArrays[2], unionArrays[1], maxObjectSize);
3740 for (size_t i = 0; i < maxObjectSize; i++)
3741 {
3742 if (dotProduct < 0)
3743 resultArray[i].setFConst(unionArrays[0][i].getFConst());
3744 else
3745 resultArray[i].setFConst(-unionArrays[0][i].getFConst());
3746 }
3747 break;
3748 }
3749
3750 case EOpRefract:
3751 {
3752 ASSERT(basicType == EbtFloat);
3753 // genType refract(genType I, genType N, float eta) :
3754 // For the incident vector I and surface normal N, and the ratio of indices of
3755 // refraction eta,
3756 // return the refraction vector. The result is computed by
3757 // k = 1.0 - eta * eta * (1.0 - dot(N, I) * dot(N, I))
3758 // if (k < 0.0)
3759 // return genType(0.0)
3760 // else
3761 // return eta * I - (eta * dot(N, I) + sqrt(k)) * N
3762 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[maxObjectSize];
3763 float dotProduct = VectorDotProduct(unionArrays[1], unionArrays[0], maxObjectSize);
3764 for (size_t i = 0; i < maxObjectSize; i++)
3765 {
3766 float eta = unionArrays[2][i].getFConst();
3767 float k = 1.0f - eta * eta * (1.0f - dotProduct * dotProduct);
3768 if (k < 0.0f)
3769 resultArray[i].setFConst(0.0f);
3770 else
3771 resultArray[i].setFConst(eta * unionArrays[0][i].getFConst() -
3772 (eta * dotProduct + sqrtf(k)) *
3773 unionArrays[1][i].getFConst());
3774 }
3775 break;
3776 }
3777 case EOpBitfieldExtract:
3778 {
3779 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[maxObjectSize];
3780 for (size_t i = 0; i < maxObjectSize; ++i)
3781 {
3782 int offset = unionArrays[1][0].getIConst();
3783 int bits = unionArrays[2][0].getIConst();
3784 if (bits == 0)
3785 {
3786 if (aggregate->getBasicType() == EbtInt)
3787 {
3788 resultArray[i].setIConst(0);
3789 }
3790 else
3791 {
3792 ASSERT(aggregate->getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
3793 resultArray[i].setUConst(0);
3794 }
3795 }
3796 else if (offset < 0 || bits < 0 || offset >= 32 || bits > 32 || offset + bits > 32)
3797 {
3798 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(loc, op, aggregate->getBasicType(), diagnostics,
3799 &resultArray[i]);
3800 }
3801 else
3802 {
3803 // bits can be 32 here, so we need to avoid bit shift overflow.
3804 uint32_t maskMsb = 1u << (bits - 1);
3805 uint32_t mask = ((maskMsb - 1u) | maskMsb) << offset;
3806 if (aggregate->getBasicType() == EbtInt)
3807 {
3808 uint32_t value = static_cast<uint32_t>(unionArrays[0][i].getIConst());
3809 uint32_t resultUnsigned = (value & mask) >> offset;
3810 if ((resultUnsigned & maskMsb) != 0)
3811 {
3812 // The most significant bits (from bits+1 to the most significant bit)
3813 // should be set to 1.
3814 uint32_t higherBitsMask = ((1u << (32 - bits)) - 1u) << bits;
3815 resultUnsigned |= higherBitsMask;
3816 }
3817 resultArray[i].setIConst(static_cast<int32_t>(resultUnsigned));
3818 }
3819 else
3820 {
3821 ASSERT(aggregate->getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
3822 uint32_t value = unionArrays[0][i].getUConst();
3823 resultArray[i].setUConst((value & mask) >> offset);
3824 }
3825 }
3826 }
3827 break;
3828 }
3829 case EOpBitfieldInsert:
3830 {
3831 resultArray = new TConstantUnion[maxObjectSize];
3832 for (size_t i = 0; i < maxObjectSize; ++i)
3833 {
3834 int offset = unionArrays[2][0].getIConst();
3835 int bits = unionArrays[3][0].getIConst();
3836 if (bits == 0)
3837 {
3838 if (aggregate->getBasicType() == EbtInt)
3839 {
3840 int32_t base = unionArrays[0][i].getIConst();
3841 resultArray[i].setIConst(base);
3842 }
3843 else
3844 {
3845 ASSERT(aggregate->getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
3846 uint32_t base = unionArrays[0][i].getUConst();
3847 resultArray[i].setUConst(base);
3848 }
3849 }
3850 else if (offset < 0 || bits < 0 || offset >= 32 || bits > 32 || offset + bits > 32)
3851 {
3852 UndefinedConstantFoldingError(loc, op, aggregate->getBasicType(), diagnostics,
3853 &resultArray[i]);
3854 }
3855 else
3856 {
3857 // bits can be 32 here, so we need to avoid bit shift overflow.
3858 uint32_t maskMsb = 1u << (bits - 1);
3859 uint32_t insertMask = ((maskMsb - 1u) | maskMsb) << offset;
3860 uint32_t baseMask = ~insertMask;
3861 if (aggregate->getBasicType() == EbtInt)
3862 {
3863 uint32_t base = static_cast<uint32_t>(unionArrays[0][i].getIConst());
3864 uint32_t insert = static_cast<uint32_t>(unionArrays[1][i].getIConst());
3865 uint32_t resultUnsigned =
3866 (base & baseMask) | ((insert << offset) & insertMask);
3867 resultArray[i].setIConst(static_cast<int32_t>(resultUnsigned));
3868 }
3869 else
3870 {
3871 ASSERT(aggregate->getBasicType() == EbtUInt);
3872 uint32_t base = unionArrays[0][i].getUConst();
3873 uint32_t insert = unionArrays[1][i].getUConst();
3874 resultArray[i].setUConst((base & baseMask) |
3875 ((insert << offset) & insertMask));
3876 }
3877 }
3878 }
3879 break;
3880 }
3881
3882 default:
3883 UNREACHABLE();
3884 return nullptr;
3885 }
3886 return resultArray;
3887}
3888
3889bool TIntermConstantUnion::IsFloatDivision(TBasicType t1, TBasicType t2)
3890{
3891 ImplicitTypeConversion conversion = GetConversion(t1, t2);
3892 ASSERT(conversion != ImplicitTypeConversion::Invalid);
3893 if (conversion == ImplicitTypeConversion::Same)
3894 {
3895 if (t1 == EbtFloat)
3896 return true;
3897 return false;
3898 }
3899 ASSERT(t1 == EbtFloat || t2 == EbtFloat);
3900 return true;
3901}
